Enjoy life's journey; but leave no tracks. Shanti'.

image.alt_text: Photo by Jaguar Siembra, Natur & Kultur in Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta. May be an image of 1 person, standing, outdoors and tree.
image.caption:
At the beginning of the creation of the world, the mountain ranges were created, the hills of the Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta that are sacred. For me they are gods that are seen as the houses of a town, because the first thing that was born was the thought of the hills. That thought originated when there was nothing and everything was mist.⁣
⁣
The hills that were born first are fathers of everything: animals, peoples, plants, waters; in them the universe is represented, in the hills the different races were born, the different peoples. The mamo began to think and saw that it was difficult for everyone to live here, since at that time the whites reproduced quickly and since they would not fit in the Sierra, he turned to Serankua, Ñankwa and Seukukuy who are the creative power of the world and they're here. As we have to share the land, the world was divided and Serankua began to create more lands for them to live outside the Black Line and receiving the advice of the mamos who met to guide them to live in other places outside of our sacred territory.⁣
⁣
Words by Mamo Mayor Zäreymakú (Juan Marcos Pérez) Kankurwa Mamingueka⁣

In the photo: Reynel Villafaña by @atasanty

image.alt_text: Photo shared by Poncho's Tlayudas on December 27, 2021 tagging @janet_mart_, @odilia_yego, and @mycielo_org. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'EL PAIS Opinión Odilia activista por defensa elos derechos lingüísticos Estados Unido DAMIAN DOVARGANES(AP En agosto de 1981 era una niña que vivía en Sierra Norte de Oaxaca en un pueblo llamado San Bartolomé Zoogocho. Tenía 10 años de edad para mí no existía otro mundo más allá de mi pueblo, sus montañas, su río, sus veredas, sus fiestas, sus tradiciones, sus colores comidas las cuales, a pesar del paso del tiempo, tengo tan presentes mi mente. El idioma universal era el zapoteco.'.
image.caption:
Have you meet @odilia_yego  and the @mycielo_org  team ?  They are must meet team. They are doing amazing work on indigenous peoples human rights ✊🏾#Repost @mycielo_org
